Core:Properties.Core:Property: "string detail;\\r\\n/* check if they are leaving for an AA, and if so, what we need to do */\\r\\n\\r\\n/* sanity checking */\\r\\nif(!\$target) return TRUE;\\r\\n\\r\\ndetail = NRefDetail(\$target);\\r\\n\\r\\n/* a sequence of ifs. Can't use switch because of delays */\\r\\nif(detail == \"path-marsh\") \{\\r\\n /* do we need to create a new adventure? */\\r\\n if(\$dest \&\& NRefOb(\$dest) == \$\{Ironclaw:AAs:Framework:RandomRoom\}) \{\\r\\n \$this.\"details:path-marsh:exit:dest:local\" = Call(\$\{Ironclaw:AAs:Framework:AdventureDB\}, \"createadventure\", \$entrance: \$this, \$adventure: \"marsh\", \$debugger: nil);\\r\\n /* delay them then re-enter the marsh */\\r\\n \$delay(1, FALSE, \"283f\");\\r\\n /* re-enter the path */\\r\\n if(!\$imperative) \{\\r\\n Act(\$actor, \"enter\", \$what: \$target);\\r\\n \} else \{\\r\\n Social(\$actor, \$imperative, \$adverb, \$evoke, \$(gait_exit:preposition), \$target);\\r\\n \}\\r\\n return FALSE;\\r\\n \}\\r\\n NRefOb(\$this.\"details:path-marsh:exit:dest:local\").\"aa:settings\".members \|= (\{ NRefOb(\$actor) \});\\r\\n \$this.\"aa:marsh:closetime\" = time()+10*2; /* close in two hours */\\r\\n \$delay(10*3, TRUE, \"b56b\"); /* wait three hours */\\r\\n /* if it's time to close, close the adventure (so a new one can be created) */\\r\\n if(!\$this.\"aa:marsh:closetime\" \|\| time() \> \$this.\"aa:marsh:closetime\") \{\\r\\n \$this.\"details:path-marsh:exit:dest:local\" = NewNRef(\$\{Ironclaw:AAs:Framework:RandomRoom\}, \"default\");\\r\\n \}\\r\\n return TRUE;\\r\\n break;\\r\\n\}\\r\\n\\r\\nreturn TRUE;"
